This paper deals with the coexistence of LTE-U and WiFi over unlicensed bands, which is a topic related to network protocols and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a game theoretic approach to resource allocation, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses optimization techniques, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of ensuring that WiFi users are not jeopardized, which is a security concern and falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
